    "Prior nutrition-focused research indicated that ChatGPT was accurate in most nutrition instances, but the chatbot also recorded errors that could potentially harm and negatively impact the end-users.",
    "Therefore, achieving general accuracy is insufficient for practical real-world applications.",
    "For example, Sun et al.",
